Class Bindings<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V>

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.qualifier.Bindings<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - the type borne by the keys of the entries in this Bindings
V - the type borne by the values of the entries in this Bindings
All Implemented Interfaces:
Constable, Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>
Direct Known Subclasses:
Qualifiers
public abstract class Bindings<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V> extends Object implements Constable, Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>
An abstract, Constable, immutable, sorted set of key-value pairs that can be used to further refine an object for many different purposes.

Keys are sorted according to their natural order.

This is a value-based class.

Values of type K must be members of classes adhering to value-based semantics.

Values of type V must be members of classes adhering to value-based semantics.

Undefined behavior will result if the preceding requirements are not honored.

Author:
Laird Nelson

      copy - if false, the supplied Maps will not be copied and will be stored by reference; it is recommended to supply true for this parameter in all but the most specific circumstances

    • contains

      public final boolean contains(Bindings<?,?> other)
      Returns true if this Bindings logically contains the supplied Bindings.

      A Bindings is said to contain another Bindings if either:

      • the two Bindings instances are identical, or
      • the size of the first Bindings is greater than the size of the second Bindings, and the entry set of this Bindings contains all of the entries in the second Bindings' entry set
      Parameters:
      other - the Bindings to test; must not be null
      Returns:
      true if this Bindings logically contains the supplied Bindings
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if other is null
      See Also:
      • Map.size()
      • Set.containsAll(java.util.Collection)
      Idempotency:
      This method is idempotent and deterministic.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.

    • symmetricDifferenceSize

      public final int symmetricDifferenceSize(Bindings<?,?> other)
      Returns the size of the symmetric difference between this Bindings and the supplied Bindings.

      The number returned is always 0 or greater.

      The size of the symmetric difference between two Bindings instances is the number of qualifier entries that are in one Bindings instance but not in the other.

      Parameters:
      other - the other Bindings instance; may be null
      Returns:
      the size of the symmetric difference between this Bindings and the supplied Bindings; always 0 or greater
      Idempotency:
      This method is idempotent and deterministic.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.
